parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive Oil Consumption and Engine Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive oil consumption can cause engine failure, leading to sudden loss of power and potential accidents, especially on highways.
symptoms: The engine consumes oil at an alarming rate
often requiring frequent oil changes; the vehicle may stall or shut down without warning; oil spots or leaks may be visible under the vehicle; the check engine light may or may not illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: PCV Valve Failure and Rear Main Seal Blowout
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the PCV valve can cause the rear main seal to blow out, leading to sudden loss of oil and potential engine failure, especially in cold temperatures.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit abnormal sounds
such as ticking or knocking noises; the check engine light may or may not illuminate; oil spots or leaks may be visible under the vehicle; the vehicle may stall or shut down without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause engine failure, leading to sudden loss of power and potential accidents, especially on highways.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit abnormal sounds
such as rattling or clunking noises; the check engine light may or may not illuminate; the vehicle may stall or shut down without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wipers can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents, especially during heavy rain or snowstorms.
Engine stalling and reduced power can cause accidents, leave the driver stranded, and lead to a loss of vehicle control.
Excessive oil consumption can lead to engine damage, increased emissions, and decreased fuel efficiency.
Transmission issues can cause accidents, leave the driver stranded, and lead to a loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: unable to shift out of park
delayed or sudden loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water pump failure can cause engine overheating, damage to engine components, and lead to a loss of vehicle control.
Windshield wiper failure can reduce visibility, increase the risk of accidents, and lead to a loss of vehicle control.
Electrical issues can cause unexpected vehicle behavior, increase the risk of accidents, and lead to a loss of vehicle control.
Interior issues can cause discomfort, distraction, and increase the risk of accidents.
